                                         "PostMention":  ""
                                     },
                                     {
                                         "text":  "<center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection: On Trade</b><br /><br />What is needed to conduct trade between two people? Or even, what is needed to conduct trade between two peoples?</div></div></center></p>",
                                         "source":  [

                                                    ],
                                         "date_time":  null,
                                         "isTable":  false,
                                         "imgdesc":  "",
                                         "format":  "html",
                                         "PostMention":  ""
                                     },
                                     {
                                         "text":  "#### Trade Data\n\nIf, in your response to the reflection, you thought that money and goods should be present for trade to occur, this is a good starting point.\n\nHowever, regarding money, as Dr. Bing Zhao rightly points out, some care must be taken. One of the explanations given by Dr. Zhao is the fact that Chinese copper coins cannot be studied as chronological markers, since coins minted in one dynasty could continue to be used in foreign trade in later dynasties (<htcite0>). Despite this point of caution when studying coins, there are other aspects mentioned in the article that need to be emphasized (<htcite1>):\n- Chinese coins could have been used as a secondary currency in a global trade.\n- The coins could represent the presence of Austronesians — peoples from East Asia, Oceania, and Madagascar who share a common maritime ancestry — in the Indian Ocean.\n\nRegarding products, the Chinese ceramics that appear in East Africa correspond to four distinct periods between <htdate0> and <htdate1> (<htcite2>; <htcite3>).",
                                         "source":  [
                                                        {
                                                            "type":  1,
                                                            "uuid":  "f7381734-81dc-4bef-8527-44317f40c4b4",
                                                            "text":  "Zhao, B.",
                                                            "page":  "",
                                                            "date_time":  {
                                                                              "type":  "gregory",
                                                                              "year":  "2015",
                                                                              "month":  "",
                                                                              "day":  ""
                                                                          }
                                                        },
                                                        {
                                                            "type":  1,
                                                            "uuid":  "f7381734-81dc-4bef-8527-44317f40c4b4",
                                                            "text":  "Zhao, B.",
                                                            "page":  "",
                                                            "date_time":  {
                                                                              "type":  "gregory",
                                                                              "year":  "2015",
                                                                              "month":  "",
                                                                              "day":  ""
                                                                          }
                                                        },
                                                        {
                                                            "type":  1,
                                                            "uuid":  "f7381734-81dc-4bef-8527-44317f40c4b4",
                                                            "text":  "Zhao, B.",
                                                            "page":  "",
                                                            "date_time":  {
                                                                              "type":  "gregory",
                                                                              "year":  "2015",
                                                                              "month":  "",
                                                                              "day":  ""
                                                                          }
                                                        },
                                                        {
                                                            "type":  1,
                                                            "uuid":  "0c717575-d51a-464d-9be6-8ecfda771376",
                                                            "text":  "History Tracers Team",
                                                            "page":  "Great Zimbabwe",
                                                            "date_time":  {
